==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Three-cornered
<hw>Three"-cor`nered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having three corners, or angles; <as>as, a <ex>three-cornered</ex>
hat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having three prominent
longitudinal angles; <as>as, a <ex>three-cornered</ex>
stem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Three-decker</ent>⟦br⟧
